Doctors at the Coast have said they will not back down until the government meets their demands. The doctors strike is on day 74. They said they strike might even go on until December, since it seems, that is when a solution will be found. Kenya Medical Association Coast secretary general Abidan Mwachi said the government has never been present at the negotiation table. He spoke at KMA Hall in Pandya Hospital, where more than 1,000 private, public and freelance doctors had converged.Some private hospitals remained closed from Tuesday midnight for 48 hours subject to review.The Court of Appeal yesterday released seven doctors' union officials jailed on Monday.Judges Wanjiru Karanja, Hannah Okwengu and Jamilla Mohamed directed that negotiations take place over seven days and return to court on February 23.